
EVERYDAY WORKFLOW
-----------------
git add FILE          - stage file
git add .             - stage all new, modified, and deleted
                           files in _current_ dir & subdirs
git add  -A / --all   - stages all changes in this repository, 
                           regardless of which folder you are in
git add -u / --update - stage edits & dels of files known to Git
                           but ignore new (untracked) files

git commit -m "msg"   - establish local snapshot to be pushed
git push              - send commits to GitHub

git fetch             - fetch only
git pending           - git fetch && git diff --name-only ..@{u}
git pull              - fetch and merge

git status            - status of local working tree
git diff              - unstaged changes
git diff --staged     - staged changes

CLONE REPO
----------
git clone URL         - copy repo
cd REPO               - enter directory
git status            - confirm clean 
                 ==> See: AUTHENTICATION

<BREAK>

CREATE FROM LOCAL DIRECTORY
---------------------------
git init                       - create local repo
git add .                      - stage all files
git commit -m "initial commit" - first commit
git remote add origin URL      - link GitHub  
git push -u origin main        - push initial commit
                 ==> See: AUTHENTICATION  

AUTHENTICATION  (git needs a token)
--------------
In CLI do:    (First check ~/.gitconfig for this setting)
    git config --global credential.helper store
         (tells git to store token in ~/.git-credentials)
On GitHub page go to: Settings
    -> Developer Settings -> Personal access tokens
    -> Tokens (classic) -> Generate new token (classic)
            Enter name of machine in "Note"
    Copy the token to use as pwd on CLI
            (use token as pwd on CLI)
Then: 
    git push -u origin main   #For new local source
or: git push                  #After clone and local add
    (And enter token as pwd. git stores token as above)

MISCELLANEOUS
-------------
git config --global alias.<alias_name> '!....'
Config files is ~/.gitconfig
